qas.question: When did Musharraf arrest Maulana Masood Azhar?
What group did Maulana Masood Azhar lead?
What group did Hafiz Muhammad Saeed lead?
What nationality is Zayn al-Abidn Muhammed Hasayn Abu Zubaydah?
Which third-highest-ranking al-Qaeda officer was captured?
Who led all of the jihadi organizations?
How many government officials were taken into custody?

plausible_answers.text: Zayn al-Abidn Muhammed Hasayn Abu Zubaydah

qas.question: What was the name of the Pakistani official that performed a number of raids?
What is the nationality of Ramzi bin al-Shibh?
What was the rank of Ramzi bin al-Shibh?

context: In <a0_0>2002<a0_0/>, the <b5_0>Musharraf<b5_0/>-led government took a firm stand against the jihadi organizations and groups promoting extremism, and arrested Maulana Masood Azhar, head of the <a1_0>Jaish-e-Mohammed<a1_0/>, and Hafiz Muhammad Saeed, chief of the <a2_0>Lashkar-e-Taiba<a2_0/>, and took <b6_0>dozens<b6_0/> of activists into custody. An official ban was imposed on the groups on 12 January. Later that year, the <a3_0><b8_0>Saudi<b8_0/><a3_0/> born <b7_0>Zayn al-Abidn Muhammed Hasayn Abu Zubaydah<b7_0/> was arrested by Pakistani officials during a series of joint U.S.-Pakistan raids. Zubaydah is said to have been a high-ranking al-Qaeda official with the title of operations chief and in charge of running al-Qaeda training camps. Other prominent al-Qaeda members were arrested in the following two years, namely Ramzi bin al-Shibh, who is known to have been a financial backer of al-Qaeda operations, and <a4_0>Khalid Sheikh Mohammed<a4_0/>, who at the time of his capture was the <b9_0>third highest-ranking<b9_0/> official in al-Qaeda and had been directly in charge of the planning for the 11 September attacks.
